Documents outlining the [MISC Israeli] proposal to allow the international transfer of nuclear technology to States that have not signed on to nonproliferation rules were distributed to the [ORG Nuclear Suppliers Group] . 
The proposal may complicate the [PER Bush] administration 's efforts to win an exemption for [LOC India] to engage in nuclear trade . 
[MISC Israeli] officials convinced a key group of nations engaged in nuclear trade to adopt new guidelines allowing the international transfer of nuclear technology to States that have not signed on to nonproliferation rules . 
[LOC Countries] including [LOC India] , [LOC Israel] and [LOC Pakistan] that have not signed the nuclear [ORG Non-Proliferation Treaty] are prohibited from participating in international nuclear trade which includes purchasing reactors , uranium fuel or yellowcake . 
Documents outlining the [MISC Israeli] proposal were distributed to the 45-member [ORG Nuclear Suppliers Group] ( [ORG NSG] ) in March 2007 . 
The [MISC Israeli] presentation was made in a nonpaper that allows for official deniability . 
According to a letter from the Chairman of the [LOC NSG] on 17 March 2007 the [MISC Israeli] presentation was offered in the context of the [LOC NSG] 's debate over [MISC Indian] officials' bid for an exemption . 
Among the nations that have not signed the [LOC Treaty] only [LOC India] and [LOC Israel] would qualify for admission to the [ORG NSG] under the [MISC Israeli] proposal . 
The [MISC Israeli] plan offered 12 criteria for allowing nuclear trade with non-treaty states . 
1 criterion indicated [LOC Israel] 's status as an undeclared nuclear weapons state and said a State should be allowed to engage in nuclear trade if the State applies stringent physical protection , control and accountancy measures to all nuclear weapons , nuclear facilities , source material and special nuclear material in the State 's territory . 
The documents circulated on [LOC Capitol Hill] in September 2007 as the [PER Bush] administration worked toward an agreement with [MISC Indian] officials . 
Executive Director of the [ORG Arms Control Association] in [LOC Washington Daryl Kimball] stated the [MISC Israeli] document could affect the debate over [LOC India] . 
[ORG Kimball] stated -- 
The dynamics at the [LOC NSG] are that officials from the countries do not want to be obstacles to [LOC India] which is the largest country and the [LOC United States] which is the most powerful country . 
Consensus on [LOC India] will be difficult to reach when the [ORG NSG] meets in November 2007 . 
[LOC Israel] 's proposal gives officials from some countries reason to suggest an alternative approach to a specific exemption . 
[LOC Israel] 's record is good and better than [LOC India] 's in following international nuclear rules . 
Despite ties between [MISC Israeli] and [LOC U.S.] governments the [ORG Bush Administration] rejected the [MISC Israeli] proposal . 
