President [PER Bush] and Secretary of State [PER Condoleezza Rice] view the Pact as an important part of the [PER Bush] administration 's foreign policy legacy . 
The deal is controversial in [LOC India] and [ORG Congress] must give approval . 
Delays in winning approval for the [LOC India] deal could have a negative effect on the administration 's foreign policy legacy with delay until an election year having the most negative effect . 
[ORG State Department] spokesman [PER Tom Casey] stated the [LOC U.S.] government views the [LOC India] deal as unique and does not see the deal as a precedent for any other country including [LOC Israel] . 
