[LOC Iran] ( [ORG IR] ) 
International ; proliferation 
Ahmadinejad announces expansion of [MISC Iranian] uranium-producing capability . 
[LOC Iran] refuses commitment to halt expansion but hints a possible future halt . 
20080726 [MISC Iranian] President [PER Mahmoud ahmadinejad] stated to scholars in the northeastern city of [LOC mashbad] that [LOC Iran] had expanded its arsenal of centrifuges producing enriched uranium to over 5000 . 
The statement was ahmadinejad 's first asserting an expansion since the 20080400 announcement that [LOC Iran] was approaching the implementation of 6000 centrifuges . 
[LOC Iran] articulated the goal of 50000 centrifuges operating at the enrichment plant near the town of [LOC Natanz] . 
The international community has demanded that [LOC Iran] halt the production of nuclear material . 
Media reports differed on the number of centrifuges ahmadinejad cited . 
An [MISC Iranian] news agency reported that ahmadinejad stated [LOC Iran] had 6000 working centrifuges but the agency subsequently removed the statement from the [MISC Internet] . 
Another [MISC Iranian] news agency stated that ahmadinejad referred to 100000s of centrifuges . 
Experts discounted the significance of ahmadinejad 's claim in the absence of information on the centrifuges' functionality . 
A [MISC Western] diplomat in [LOC Tehran] speaking under condition of anonymity stated that the quantity of centrifuges is less important than whether the machines are operational and efficient but that ahmadinejad 's assertion will hinder a resolution of the diplomatic standoff between [LOC Iran] and the [LOC West] . 
Arms control expert [PER Jeffrey G. Lewis] of the new [LOC America] [ORG Foundation] think tank stated that the [ORG Foundation] was aware of [LOC Iran] 's goal of assembling 6000 centrifuges but the operational status of the machines is unknown . 
Diplomats and arms control experts stated that the [MISC Iranian] enrichment program is hindered by technical problems . 
[LOC Iran] has repeatedly asserted that its nuclear program aims to produce only electricity because nuclear weapon production contradicts [MISC Islamic] principles . 
The [LOC US] , [LOC Israel] , [LOC Europe] and the majority of [MISC Western] arms control experts believe that [LOC Iran] is pursuing the capability to produce bombs immediately in the event of a decision . 
Experts stated that producing weapons-grade uranium from reactor-grade material is relatively simple . 
[PER Ahmadinejad] stated that after [LOC Iran] resisted the [LOC West] 's demands for a halt in nuclear activities , the [LOC West] still pursued the resumption of negotiations . 
[ORG EU] foreign policy chief [PER Javier Solana] recently presented [LOC Iran] with 2 offers -- 
A US-endorsed package of incentives to cease enriched uranium production 
A 6-week pre-negotiation' freeze for freeze' period during which [LOC Iran] would add no centrifuges and the [LOC West] would refrain from promoting a 4th round of economic sanctions against [LOC Iran] at the [ORG UN Security Council] . 
[LOC US] officials repeatedly stated that no negotiations can begin before [LOC Iran] verifiably halts all enrichment-related activities but the [PER Bush] administration recently agreed to the' freeze for freeze' proposal and dispatch burns to [LOC Geneva] . 
20080726 during talks in [LOC Geneva] attended by [ORG US Undersecretary of State] [PER William J. Burns] [LOC Iran] refused to respond to [PER Solana] 's offers . 
The talks constituted the highest-level diplomatic contact between the [LOC US] and [LOC Iran] for nearly 30 years . 
[LOC Solana] , burns and [MISC European] envoys set a deadline for [LOC Iran] to respond positively before initiating new sanctions including prohibitions on selling [LOC Iran] refined petroleum products vital to the country 's economy . 
[MISC Iranian] officials refused to commit to stopping expansion or to observe the deadline . 
20080726 ahmadinejad appeared to suggest that [LOC Iran] might potentially halt expansion at a higher number of centrifuges that previously expected and for over 6 weeks . 
[PER Ahmadinejad] stated that the [LOC West] had consented to the existing 5000-6000 centrifuges in operation provided that the number did not increase . 
5000 centrifuges can produce sufficient nuclear material for a power plant or an atomic bomb if the material is highly enriched . 
6000 centrifuges running continuously can produce sufficient weapons-grade uranium for 1 bomb in 6 months . 
20080500 the [ORG International Atomic Energy Agency] stated that [LOC Iran] possessed 3500 centrifuges in operations . 
